  "root_text": {
    "sn46.17:0.1": "Saṁyutta Nikāya 46.17 ",
    "sn46.17:0.2": "2. Gilānavagga ",
    "sn46.17:0.3": "Pāraṅgamasutta ",
    "sn46.17:1.1": "“Sattime, bhikkhave, bojjhaṅgā bhāvitā bahulīkatā apārā pāraṁ gamanāya saṁvattanti. ",
    "sn46.17:1.2": "Katame satta? ",
    "sn46.17:1.3": "Satisambojjhaṅgo …pe… upekkhāsambojjhaṅgo—",
    "sn46.17:1.4": "ime kho, bhikkhave, satta bojjhaṅgā bhāvitā bahulīkatā apārā pāraṁ gamanāya saṁvattantīti. ",
    "sn46.17:2.1": "Appakā te manussesu, ",
    "sn46.17:2.2": "ye janā pāragāmino; ",
    "sn46.17:2.3": "Athāyaṁ itarā pajā, ",
    "sn46.17:2.4": "tīramevānudhāvati. ",
    "sn46.17:3.1": "Ye ca kho sammadakkhāte, ",
    "sn46.17:3.2": "dhamme dhammānuvattino; ",
    "sn46.17:3.3": "Te janā pāramessanti, ",
    "sn46.17:3.4": "maccudheyyaṁ suduttaraṁ. ",
    "sn46.17:4.1": "Kaṇhaṁ dhammaṁ vippahāya, ",
    "sn46.17:4.2": "sukkaṁ bhāvetha paṇḍito; ",
    "sn46.17:4.3": "Okā anokamāgamma, ",
    "sn46.17:4.4": "viveke yattha dūramaṁ. ",
    "sn46.17:5.1": "Tatrābhiratimiccheyya, ",
    "sn46.17:5.2": "hitvā kāme akiñcano; ",
    "sn46.17:5.3": "Pariyodapeyya attānaṁ, ",
    "sn46.17:5.4": "cittaklesehi paṇḍito. ",
    "sn46.17:6.1": "Yesaṁ sambodhiyaṅgesu, ",
    "sn46.17:6.2": "sammā cittaṁ subhāvitaṁ; ",
    "sn46.17:6.3": "Ādānappaṭinissagge, ",
    "sn46.17:6.4": "anupādāya ye ratā; ",
    "sn46.17:6.5": "Khīṇāsavā jutimanto, ",
    "sn46.17:6.6": "te loke parinibbutā”ti. ",
    "sn46.17:6.7": "Sattamaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "sn46.17:0.1": "Linked Discourses 46.17 ",
    "sn46.17:0.2": "2. Sick ",
    "sn46.17:0.3": "Going to the Far Shore ",
    "sn46.17:1.1": "“Mendicants, when these seven awakening factors are developed and cultivated they lead to going from the near shore to the far shore. ",
    "sn46.17:1.2": "What seven? ",
    "sn46.17:1.3": "The awakening factors of mindfulness, investigation of principles, energy, rapture, tranquility, immersion, and equanimity. ",
    "sn46.17:1.4": "These seven awakening factors, when developed and cultivated, lead to going from the near shore to the far shore. ",
    "sn46.17:2.1": "Few are those among humans ",
    "sn46.17:2.2": "who cross to the far shore. ",
    "sn46.17:2.3": "The rest just run ",
    "sn46.17:2.4": "around on the near shore. ",
    "sn46.17:3.1": "When the teaching is well explained, ",
    "sn46.17:3.2": "those who practice accordingly ",
    "sn46.17:3.3": "are the ones who will cross over ",
    "sn46.17:3.4": "Death’s dominion so hard to pass. ",
    "sn46.17:4.1": "Rid of dark qualities, ",
    "sn46.17:4.2": "an astute person should develop the bright. ",
    "sn46.17:4.3": "Leaving home behind ",
    "sn46.17:4.4": "for the seclusion so hard to enjoy, ",
    "sn46.17:5.1": "try to find satisfaction there, ",
    "sn46.17:5.2": "having left behind sensual pleasures. ",
    "sn46.17:5.3": "Owning nothing, an astute person ",
    "sn46.17:5.4": "should cleanse themselves of mental corruptions. ",
    "sn46.17:6.1": "And those whose minds are rightly developed ",
    "sn46.17:6.2": "in the awakening factors; ",
    "sn46.17:6.3": "letting go of attachments, ",
    "sn46.17:6.4": "they delight in not grasping. ",
    "sn46.17:6.5": "With defilements ended, brilliant, ",
    "sn46.17:6.6": "they are quenched in this world.” "
  },
